{"parse":{"title":"Nomad studies","pageid":56258775,"revid":841246369,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Nomad studies</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Russian_language\" title=\"Russian language\">Russian</a>: <span lang=\"ru\">\u041a\u043e\u0447\u0435\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435</span>, kochevnikovedenie; <a href=\"/wiki/Russian_language\" title=\"Russian language\">Russian</a>: <span lang=\"ru\">\u041d\u043e\u043c\u0430\u0434\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u043a\u0430</span>, nomadistika) is branch of historical and anthropological studies specialised in cultures and history of <a href=\"/wiki/Nomad\" title=\"Nomad\">nomad</a> peoples, particularly the <a href=\"/wiki/Eurasian_nomads\" title=\"Eurasian nomads\">Eurasian nomads</a> and history of the <a href=\"/wiki/Eurasian_steppes\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Eurasian steppes\">Eurasian steppes</a>. Studies of the <a href=\"/wiki/Eurasian_nomads\" title=\"Eurasian nomads\">Eurasian nomads</a> influence the political idea of <a href=\"/wiki/Eurasianism\" title=\"Eurasianism\">Eurasianism</a>.\n</p><p>Among notable researchers in that field were <a href=\"/wiki/Lev_Gumilyov\" title=\"Lev Gumilyov\">Lev Gumilyov</a>, Pyotr Savitskiy, <a href=\"/wiki/Sergei_Rudenko\" title=\"Sergei Rudenko\">Sergei Rudenko</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/George_Vernadsky\" title=\"George Vernadsky\">George Vernadsky</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Nikolai_Trubetzkoy\" title=\"Nikolai Trubetzkoy\">Nikolai Trubetzkoy</a>, Hara-Davan Erendzhen, <a href=\"/wiki/Mikhail_Illarionovich_Artamonov\" title=\"Mikhail Illarionovich Artamonov\">Mikhail Artamonov</a>, and others.\n</p><p>According to Savitskiy, the history of <a href=\"/wiki/Scythian\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Scythian\">Scythians</a> and huns encompasses in general (within historically foreseeable events) over 12 centuries. Savitskiy claims that the nomad culture of Scythians and Huns should be considered as culture of horse and iron.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Nomad_studies&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20180109165018/https://www.caravan.kz/articles/istoricheskaya-nauka-na-povestke-dnya-kochevnikovedenie-366871/\">Historical Studies: on daily agenda nomadic studies (\u0418\u0441\u0442\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0430\u044f \u043d\u0430\u0443\u043a\u0430: \u043d\u0430 \u043f\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0441\u0442\u043a\u0435 \u0434\u043d\u044f \u043a\u043e\u0447\u0435\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0435)</a>. Caravan Media Portal. 3 December 2007</li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20180109165250/https://www.csen.org/\">Official website</a>. The Center for the Study of Eurasian Nomads (part of the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=American-Eurasian_Research_Institute&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"American-Eurasian Research Institute (page does not exist)\">American-Eurasian Research Institute</a>)</li>\n<li><span class=\"languageicon\">(in Russian)</span> Savitskiy, P.N. <i><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20180109170810/http://gumilevica.kulichki.net/SPN/spn01.htm\">About issues of nomad studies (Why Scythians and Huns must be of interest for Russians (\u041e \u0437\u0430\u0434\u0430\u0447\u0430\u0445 \u043a\u043e\u0447\u0435\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0438\u044f (\u041f\u043e\u0447\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u0441\u043a\u0438\u0444\u044b \u0438 \u0433\u0443\u043d\u043d\u044b \u0434\u043e\u043b\u0436\u043d\u044b \u0431\u044b\u0442\u044c \u0438\u043d\u0442\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0441\u043d\u044b \u0434\u043b\u044f \u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e?))</a></i>. Eurasian Publishing (by kulichki). Prague, 1928.</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mw2236\nCached time: 20180921192613\nCache expiry: 1900800\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.164 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.205 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 64/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 0/1500000\nPost\u2010expand include size: 1055/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 8/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 9/40\nExpensive parser function count: 1/500\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post\u2010expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\nNumber of Wikibase entities loaded: 0/400\nLua time usage: 0.136/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 8.78 MB/50 MB\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%  195.084      1 -total\n 84.94%  165.700      2 Template:Lang-ru\n 14.97%   29.196      1 Template:Ru_icon\n 14.25%   27.807      1 Template:Link_language\n  8.70%   16.979      1 Template:Category_handler\n  0.71%    1.393      2 Template:ISO_639_name_ru\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key enwiki:pcache:idhash:56258775-0!canonical and timestamp 20180921192612 and revision id 841246369\n -->\n</div>"},"langlinks":[],"categories":[{"sortkey":"","hidden":"","*":"Articles_containing_Russian-language_text"},{"sortkey":"","hidden":"","*":"Articles_with_Russian-language_external_links"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Eurasia"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Eurasian_history"},{"sortkey":"","*":"World_history"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Eurasianism"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Nomads"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Nomadic_groups_in_Eurasia"},{"sortkey":"","*":"Oriental_studies"}],"links":[{"ns":10,"exists":"","*":"Template:ISO 639 name ru"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Eurasian nomads"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Eurasian steppes"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Eurasianism"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"George Vernadsky"},{"ns":0,"exists":"","*":"Lev Gumilyov"},{"ns":0,"exists":""